quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  41,30,"Indeed those who say, ‘Our Lord is Allah!’ and then remain steadfast, the angels descend upon them, [saying,] ‘Do not fear, nor be grieved! Receive the good news of the paradise, which you have been promised"
  41,31,"We are your friends in the life of this world and in the Hereafter, and you will have in it whatever your souls desire, and you will have in it whatever you ask for"
  41,32,"as a hospitality from One all-forgiving, all-merciful.’"
  41,33,"Who has a better call than him who summons to Allah and acts righteously and says, ‘Indeed I am one of the Muslims’"
  41,34,"Good and evil [conduct] are not equal. Repel [evil] with what is best. [If you do so,] he between whom and you was enmity, will then be as though he were a sympathetic friend"
  41,35,"But none is granted it except those who are patient, and none is granted it except the greatly endowed"
  41,36,"Should an incitement from Satan prompt you [to ill feeling], seek the protection of Allah. Indeed, He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing"
  41,37,"Among His signs are night and day, and the sun and the moon. Do not prostrate to the sun, nor to the moon, but prostrate to Allah who created them, if it is Him that you worship"
  41,38,"But if they disdain [the worship of Allah], those who are near your Lord glorify Him night and day, and they are not wearied"